curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/13692' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM48000/SGM48001/SGM48002", "table_name": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION", "content": "GENERAL DESCRIPTION  The SGM48000/1/2 series are dual-channel low-side  drivers with typical 2A source and sink current  capability. Inverting and non-inverting inputs are both  available and three combinations can be chosen for  flexible logic application.  The rise time and fall time of SGM48000/1/2 are  matched to be 12ns and 13ns respectively, which  allows the pulse widths to deliver to the outputs with  minimum timing errors and clock skew issues. Unique  technique is integrated to achieve minimum overlap of  the outputs, which reduces the dynamic switching  losses.  The SGM48000/1/2 are available in Green SOIC-8 and  TDFN-2×2-8L packages. They operate over an ambient  temperature range of -40℃ to +125℃.    "}'
curl -XPOST 'http://localhost:9200/electronic_products/_create/13693' -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"product_name": "SGM48000/SGM48001/SGM48002", "table_name": "FEATURES", "content": "FEATURES  ● Improved Response Times  ● Matched Rise and Fall Times  ● Reduced Clock Skew between Dual Channels  ● Low Output Impedance  ● Output is at LOW under UVLO Protection  ● High Noise Immunity  ● Improved Clocking Rate  ● Low Supply Current  ● Wide Operating Voltage Range  ● -40℃ to +125℃ Operating Temperature Range  ● Available in Green SOIC-8 and TDFN-2×2-8L  Packages      "}'
